name: Sainsbury Centre for Visual Arts
directions: Turn left immediately after you go in via the main entrance, the toilets are at the front of the building just past a small seating area.
comment: There are three individual toilets, each one contains your own private toilet, sink, paper towels, waste bin and huge mirror. A bit more floor space than your usual cubicle toilet. Automatic lights that switch on when you lock the door from the inside. No noise privacy, you CAN hear the person in the next cubicle when they make noise.  You can almost certainly get away with not paying for gallery entry as the gallery has a 'look around for free' option

As you walk in the area with the "Women's Restroom" sign, the accessible gender-neutral restroom is to the right. There will be a sign on the wall directing towards it.
